# Architecture Review Bridge

Owner must NOT act as manual relay between Cursor and ChatGPT.

## When to escalate

Create a review request when ANY apply:

- confidence is `experimental`, `unstable`, or `blocked`
- architecture uncertain (storage, lifecycle, distributed sync)
- runtime risk high (Android FGS, headless, overlay)
- dependency conflict in `strategic-priorities.json` dependencyGraph
- scaling risk (storage growth, payload size)

## How to escalate (do NOT message owner to forward)

```bash
npm run review:request -- \
  --template gps-storage \
  --title "..." \
  --subsystem background-drive \
  --reasoning "..." \
  --architecture-concern "..." \
  --proposed-direction "..." \
  --confidence experimental
```

Or POST `/api/architecture-reviews` with header `X-Aion-Agent-Key: $OPERATIONS_OWNER_SECRET`.

## Rules

- Do NOT freeze entire autonomous loop — continue parallel roadmap priorities
- Copy review packet from portal `/operations/review-queue` or API response `reviewPacketMarkdown`
- On resolution: PATCH `/api/architecture-reviews/[id]` with result; link commits via `--commits`
- Append feed after major implementation regardless

## Portal surfaces

- `/operations/reviews` — history + templates
- `/operations/review-queue` — pending/reviewing
- `/api/architecture-reviews`
